# Root Directory

## 📁 Core Folders

- 📄 /briefs
    
    All legal briefs, complaints, motions, and memoranda
    
    Naming: YYYY-MM-DD_Document-Type_v#.pdf
    
- 📎 /appendix
    
    Supporting appendices and supplemental materials
    
- ➕ /addendum
    
    Additional materials and amendments
    
- 🎤 /oa
    
    Opening arguments and oral argument materials
    
- ⚖️ /orders
    
    Court orders and proposed orders
    
    Draft orders ready for signature
    
- 🧰 /kits
    
    Reusable templates and relief banks
    
    Filing checklists and quick-reference cards
    
- 📢 /release
    
    Public release materials
    
    Press kits and public-facing documents
    
- 🗄️ /archive
    
    Complete case archive with subfolders (see below)
    

## 📄 Root Files

- **index.html** — Main navigation page
- **Master_Index.csv** — Complete document index
- **Start_Here.html** — Quick-start guide
- **CHECKSUMS.txt** — SHA-256 hashes for verification
- **CHANGELOG.md** — Version history and updates

---

# Archive Folder Structure

Location: `/archive/`

## Public Folder

- **/Public/Exhibits** — PDF-A format with Bates numbering
- **/Public/Index** — CSV and JSON indexes
- **/Public/Summaries** — 2-pagers and FAQs

## Restricted Folder

- **/Restricted/Unredacted** — Access-controlled sensitive materials
- **/Restricted/Legal_Work_Product** — Attorney work product

## Press Kit Folder

- **/Press_Kit/OnePager.pdf** — 1-page case summary
- **/Press_Kit/Timeline.png** — Visual timeline
- **/Press_Kit/Top10_Exhibits.pdf** — Key evidence highlights

---

# Case Archive Subfolders

Location: `/archive/Case_Archive/`

- **00_Timeline/** — Timeline.csv with key dates
- **01_Pleadings/** — All filed pleadings
- **02_Exhibits/** — Bates-numbered exhibits (Bates_0001-000N)
- **03_Orders/** — Court orders and judgments
- **04_Notices/** — Notices of filing and service
- **05_FOIA/** — FOIA requests and responses

---

# File Naming Conventions

<aside>
**Best Practices:**
Date-stamp all files: YYYY-MM-DD_Document-Name_v#.pdf
Keep consistent slugs for easy searching
Include version numbers for drafts
Export final versions as PDF-A for permanence

</aside>

---

# Quick Setup Checklist

- [ ]  Create root folders: briefs, appendix, addendum, oa, orders, kits, release, archive
- [ ]  Create root files: index.html, Master_Index.csv, Start_Here.html, CHECKSUMS.txt, [CHANGELOG.md](http://CHANGELOG.md)
- [ ]  Set up /archive/ with Public, Restricted, Press_Kit subfolders
- [ ]  Create Case_Archive with 00–05 numbered folders
- [ ]  Seed Timeline.csv with 5 key dates
- [ ]  Add initial [CHANGELOG.md](http://CHANGELOG.md) entry
- [ ]  Set permissions: Public = read-only, Restricted = access-controlled

<aside>
**Purpose:** This structure makes collaboration scalable, ensures portability, and maintains verifiability across all filings and appeals.

</aside>